        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>unites the two sets containing given elements WITHOUT balancing by set size (BaseUnionFind keeps no sizes):
it simply attaches one set&apos;s root under the other&apos;s, so chained calls can build taller trees.
Prefer UnionFind::unite, which selects the new root by set size, when many unions follow one another.
\\return first: new common root, second: true if the union was done (false if already in one set)
</verbatim> </para>
        </detaileddescription>
